attab", "runs": [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}, {"text": "3", "runs": [{"text": "3", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}]], "images": [], "notes": null}, {"slide_number": 4, "title": "Muddiest Points (Banker\u2019s Algorithm)", "text_blocks": [[{"text": "Muddiest Points (Banker\u2019s Algorithm)", "runs": [{"text": "Muddiest Points (Banker\u2019s Algorithm)", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 43.98}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "what are the three steps of the bankers algorithm?", "runs": [{"text": "what are the three steps of the bankers algorithm?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "Could you go over the Bankers algorithm example again?", "runs": [{"text": "Could you go over the Bankers algorithm example again?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "For the safe/unsafe algorithm, does that mean we need to know the resources that are available,", "runs": [{"text": "For the safe/unsafe algorithm, does that mean we need to know the resources that are available, ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "keep track of the used ones, and also know how many each process will have in the future?", "runs": [{"text": "keep track of the used ones, and also know how many each process will have in the future?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.02}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "It seems like this detection algorithm has a lot of overhead. Are there any ways of reducing the time", "runs": [{"text": "It seems like this detection algorithm has a lot of overhead. Are there any ways of reducing the time ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "spent doing these checks", "runs": [{"text": "spent doing these checks", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "can we run the banker's algorithm or some alternative as a static analysis tool? like build this kind of", "runs": [{"text": "can we run the banker's algorithm or some alternative as a static analysis tool? like build this kind of ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "check into the compiler or something instead of running it for each request during runtime", "runs": [{"text": "check into the compiler or something instead of running it for each request during runtime", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "If a state is determined unsafe, does that always mean that the resource will not be allocated or is it", "runs": [{"text": "If a state is determined unsafe, does that always mean that the resource will not be allocated or is it ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "possible to still allocate it and take the risk", "runs": [{"text": "possible to still allocate it and take the risk", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.02}]}, {"text": "What does the E, P and A stand for in the bankers algorithm", "runs": [{"text": "What does the E, P and A stand for in the bankers algorithm", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.02}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "if bankers algorithm finds a valid path and grants the resource, can a deadlock still occur if a different", "runs": [{"text": "if bankers algorithm finds a valid path and grants the resource, can a deadlock still occur if a different ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "path is followed than the one bankers algorithm found?", "runs": [{"text": "path is followed than the one bankers algorithm found?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "I'm a little confused on what the want and hold tables represent", "runs": [{"text": "I'm a little confused on what the want and hold tables represent", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "Why is the runtime n^2 * n for the wait algorithm", "runs": [{"text": "Why is the runtime n^2 * n for the wait algorithm", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "What is the difference between wanted and max again?", "runs": [{"text": "What is the difference between wanted and max again?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 18.0}]}, {"text": "Tracing bankers algorithms with multiple resource instances", "runs": [{"text": "Tracing bankers algorithms with multiple resource instances", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 18.0}]}], [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "runs": [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}, {"text": "4", "runs": [{"text": "4", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}]], "images": [], "notes": null}, {"slide_number": 5, "title": "Muddiest Points (Resource Trajectory)", "text_blocks": [[{"text": "Muddiest Points (Resource Trajectory)", "runs": [{"text": "Muddiest Points (Resource Trajectory)", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 43.98}]}], [{"text": "\u2022 the l1, l2 l3 ... in the resource trajectory graph", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 31.98}, {"text": " the l1, l2 l3 ... in the resource trajectory graph", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 31.98}]}], [{"text": "\u2022 resource trajectory graphs with more than 2 resources", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 32.0}, {"text": " resource trajectory graphs with more than 2 resources", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 32.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022 How to prevent a resource trajectory that would cause a", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 31.98}, {"text": " How to prevent a resource trajectory that would cause a ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 31.98}]}], [{"text": "deadlock", "runs": [{"text": "deadlock", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 31.98}]}], [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "runs": [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}, {"text": "5", "runs": [{"text": "5", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}]], "images": [], "notes": null}, {"slide_number": 6, "title": "Muddiest Points (General Deadlock)", "text_blocks": [[{"text": "Muddiest Points (General Deadlock)", "runs": [{"text": "Muddiest Points (General Deadlock)", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 43.98}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "breaking circular wait seems almost always better than breaking", "runs": [{"text": "breaking circular wait seems almost always better than breaking ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "hold and wait since breaking hold and wait requires you take all", "runs": [{"text": "hold and wait since breaking hold and wait requires you take all ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "resources you need whereas breaking circular wait only makes you", "runs": [{"text": "resources you need whereas breaking circular wait only makes you ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "take some extra resources before you need them", "runs": [{"text": "take some extra resources before you need them", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.02}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "Starvation vs deadlock", "runs": [{"text": "Starvation vs deadlock", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "Which detection alg is fastest?", "runs": [{"text": "Which detection alg is fastest?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "Where do deadlock detection algorithms exist? (Operating system", "runs": [{"text": "Where do deadlock detection algorithms exist? (Operating system ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "or external application.) When do they run? Runtime or compile", "runs": [{"text": "or external application.) When do they run? Runtime or compile ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.02}]}, {"text": "time? Also, how do deadlock avoidance algorithms interfere to", "runs": [{"text": "time? Also, how do deadlock avoidance algorithms interfere to ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "make sure a program doesn\u2019t deadlock? Are they integrated fully", "runs": [{"text": "make sure a program doesn\u2019t deadlock? Are they integrated fully ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "into the application?", "runs": [{"text": "into the application?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "how do we know what resources are available to use and the best", "runs": [{"text": "how do we know what resources are available to use and the best ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "way to choose who gets what resources", "runs": [{"text": "way to choose who gets what resources", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "What is better practice, deadlock avoidance or deadlock detection?", "runs": [{"text": "What is better practice, deadlock avoidance or deadlock detection?", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}], [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "runs": [{"text": "CS/COE 1550 \u2013 Operating Systems \u2013 Sherif Khattab", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}, {"text": "6", "runs": [{"text": "6", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT", "font_size": 13.98}]}]], "images": [], "notes": null}, {"slide_number": 7, "title": "Muddiest Points (Deadlock Prevention)", "text_blocks": [[{"text": "Muddiest Points (Deadlock Prevention)", "runs": [{"text": "Muddiest Points (Deadlock Prevention)", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 43.98}]}], [{"text": "\u2022", "runs": [{"text": "\u2022", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "ArialMT", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "When checking a program to see it is free of deadlocks, you have to", "runs": [{"text": "When checking a program to see it is free of deadlocks, you have to ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "look for whether one of the four condtions is being broken", "runs": [{"text": "look for whether one of the four condtions is being broken ", "bold": false, "italic": false, "underline": false, "font_name": "SourceSansPro-Regular", "font_size": 27.0}]}, {"text": "somewhere?", "runs": [{"text": "somewhere?", "bold": false, "italic": fal